    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into wedges</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 25-30 min or until the wedges are golden and crispy \u2013 these are your <strong>smoky wedges</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the wedges are in the oven, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> into rings</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Set aside to pickle \u2013 these are your <strong>pickled shallots</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, separate the <strong>leaves </strong>and set aside for serving then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Line a separate baking tray with <strong>baking paper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>meat-free patty[ies]</strong> to the lined tray and put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half (if required!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the patties are cooked through, remove the tray from the oven and top each patty with your <strong>cheese flavour slice[s]</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> brioche halves</strong> to the other side of the tray</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 3-4 min or until the cheese has melted and the brioche is warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/the-manilife-pbandj-meat-free-burger-with-sweet-potato-wedges/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain the <strong>pickled shallots</strong></p><p>Spread each <strong>brioche base</strong> with your <strong>mayo </strong>and each <strong>brioche lid</strong> with your<strong> red chilli relish</strong></p><p>Build your meat-free burger by topping the base with the <strong>pickled shallots</strong>, some<strong> lettuce leaves</strong>,<strong> </strong>a <strong>cheesy patty</strong>, your<strong> peanut butter </strong>and finish with the lid</p><p>Serve with the <strong>smoky wedges</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
